adjectives.description: workmanlike (comparative more workmanlike, superlative most workmanlike)

entries.meaning: Resembling or characteristic of a workman.
examples: She was dressed in khaki, khaki slacks and khaki shirt, practical and workmanlike.
The tandem arrangement does not misuse Close, for he has gotten decades of acclaim for a tedious, workmanlike art.

entries.meaning: Performed with the skill of an artisan or craftsman.
